results.name: Triangle T(n,f): the number of bicolored cubic graphs on 2n vertices with f vertices of the first color.
comment: These are connected, undirected, simple cubic graphs where each vertex has either the first or the second color. Row n has 2n+1 entries, 0<=f<=2n. The column f=0 (1, 0, 2, 5,...) counts the cubic graphs (A002851). The column f=1 (0, 1, 2, 10, 64, 490...) counts the rooted cubic graphs.
xref: Cf. A002851 (first column), A294783 (bicolored trees), A321305 (signed edges).
results.author: _R. J. Mathar_, Nov 03 2018
